Reasoning: The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning algorithms for semantic classification, which falls under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of supervised corpus-based machine learning algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper's focus on analogies and associations suggests that it may be relevant to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's use of multiple-choice questions and cognitive psychology suggests that it may also be relevant to the subfields of information retrieval (cs.IR) and cognitive computing (cs.CC).
